cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based solution for iris recognition, which involves image processing, feature extraction, and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a trainable VLAD encoder and deformable convolution, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper deals with image degradation caused by head rotation and illumination variations, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on public iris image databases, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
